items.summary:
&ldquo;Robert suggested we create Facebook accounts, I think in an effort to establish that we were &ldquo;down&rdquo; with whatever &ldquo;new jives&rdquo; the kids were flexing on the mean streets. I refused. Gabriel buckled, and the bullshit that ensued verified my initial assessment: that maintaining Facebook would quickly constitute another job. Of which I already have several.&quot;
— Tycho, Penny-Arcade
I never really bought into social networking (because I am of course antisocial) But lo and behold!
